<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-0892 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper describes the implementation of a 1150 kW Mini-Hydro generationplant at Wemindji, a remote community in Northern Canada. A number ofstudies and investigations of the overall costs of energy to the communityled to the choice of a mixed energy supply system consisting of mini-hydro,diesel and firewood. The 1150 kW mini-hydro powerplant constitutes themain element in this energy supply. Details are given of the design andimplementation of the mini-hydro power facility and its related equipment,with descriptions of constraints that were overcome from the conceptionthrough to commissioning an initial operation.</TEXT></DOC>